A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Luella High School NJROTC Program; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the Luella High School NJROTC Program was established in August 2003 at
3 Luella High School in Locust Grove, Georgia, as a vital initiative dedicated to fostering
4 leadership, citizenship, and community involvement among the school's students; and
5 WHEREAS, the program is led by Retired Lieutenant Ohmahr Fleming, Senior Naval
6 Science Instructor; Retired Master Gunnery Sergeant Gregory Hardy, Naval Science
7 Instructor; and Retired Master Sergeant David Young, Naval Science Instructor, who
8 collectively wield over 77 years of military service and expertise; and
9 WHEREAS, serving students in grades 8 through 12, the Luella High School NJROTC
10 Program annually enrolls over 170 cadets, providing them with a curriculum centered around
11 leadership development and civic responsibility; and
12 WHEREAS, cadets in the NJROTC program contribute more than 15,000 hours of
13 community service each year in support of both Henry County and the greater metro Atlanta
14 area; and
